sagma.core.math
Class Triangle

java.lang.Object
  sagma.core.math.Triangle

public class Triangle
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a physical 3D triangle A Triangle MUST be constructed with exactly 3 defined Vec3's. If any of the Vectors are null then the triangle will crash the application when accessed. Detecting null vectors is not the responsibility of this triangle. However the triangle is much more lenient when given null values for normals and texture co-ordinates. If the normal vector array is given as null, then the corresponding normals will be created when access is attempted. The normals will not be perfect, but a good enough representation. The textue co-ordinates will be generated as well if they are missing, it will be a horrible representation but sometimes you don't care. For example when it's not textured.

Author:
Aaron Kison
